# Sonic Bloom — work rules

## Source of truth

- **`AGENTS.md`** — stack, Cloudflare, auth flags, layout map, conventions. Read it when touching architecture or new areas.
- **`docs/TEST-PLAN.md`** — what we test and how to recover when CI fails.

## After substantive changes

Run **`npm run verify`** (lint → Vitest → Playwright E2E → production build) before considering work done. Fix failures using the recovery table in `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`.

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Dev (port **3000**) | `npm run dev` |
| Lint | `npm run lint` |
| Unit tests | `npm test` |
| E2E | `npm run test:e2e` |
| Full gate | `npm run verify` |

## Scope and assumptions

- UI data is **mock / in-memory** unless you explicitly wire a real API (`src/lib/mock-data.ts`, `src/lib/store.ts`).
- Do not assume real audio playback or OAuth unless implemented.
- **`lovable-tagger`** is dev-only; do not rely on it for production behavior.

## Documentation

- Do **not** add new root-level markdown guides unless the user asks. Prefer updating **`AGENTS.md`** or **`docs/TEST-PLAN.md`** when project behavior or testing changes.
